1.1.1 Key concepts
------------------

*ndarray* is the central data type - an opaque handle wrapping a dense
numeric array.  Unlike Maxima matrices, ndarrays:

   • Use *0-based indexing* (like NumPy, C, and most programming
     languages)
   • Store elements as *double-float* (64-bit IEEE 754)
   • Use *column-major* memory layout for BLAS compatibility
   • Are *mutable* - functions like ‘np_set’ modify the array in place


File: numerics.info,  Node: Quick start,  Next: Creating arrays,  Prev: Key concepts,  Up: Introduction to numerics

1.1.2 Quick start
-----------------

(%i1) load("numerics")$
(%i2) A : ndarray(matrix([1, 2], [3, 4]));
(%o2)            ndarray([2, 2], DOUBLE-FLOAT)
(%i3) B : np_inv(A);
(%o3)            ndarray([2, 2], DOUBLE-FLOAT)
(%i4) np_to_matrix(np_matmul(A, B));
(%o4)            matrix([1.0, 0.0], [0.0, 1.0])


