 -- Function: np_trapz (Y) / NP_TRAPZ (Y, X)
     Trapezoidal numerical integration of a 1D ndarray.

     Without an ‘x’ argument, uses unit spacing (dx = 1).  With an ‘x’
     argument, uses the spacing defined by the ‘x’ array.  Both ‘y’ and
     ‘x’ must be 1D ndarrays of the same length.  Returns a scalar.

     Calling forms:

        • ‘np_trapz(y)’ - integrate with unit spacing
        • ‘np_trapz(y, x)’ - integrate with variable spacing defined by
          x

