 -- Function: np_conj (A)
     Element-wise complex conjugate.

     Returns a new ndarray where each element is the complex conjugate
     of the corresponding element in ‘a’.  For real (double-float)
     arrays, this returns a copy of ‘a’ unchanged.  For complex arrays,
     conjugates each element (negates the imaginary part).

* Menu:

     * Examples::

1.3.1.81 Examples
.................

(%i1) A : ndarray(matrix([1+%i, 2-3*%i]), complex);
(%o1)     ndarray([1, 2], COMPLEX-DOUBLE-FLOAT)
(%i2) np_to_list(np_conj(A));
(%o2)              [1.0 - 1.0*%i, 2.0 + 3.0*%i]
(%i3) /* Real arrays are unchanged */
      np_to_list(np_conj(ndarray([1, 2, 3], [3])));
(%o3)                     [1.0, 2.0, 3.0]

